{
  "info": {
    "name": "Order & Payment Management API",
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "description": "A Laravel 12 REST API for managing customer Orders and processing Payments through a pluggable, multi-gateway architecture (Strategy + Factory patterns) secured with JWT authentication.\n\n## Getting Started\n1. Start the server: `php artisan serve`\n2. Select the **Order & Payment API — Local** environment.\n3. Run **Register** or **Login** — the `token` variable is set automatically and used by all protected requests.\n\n## Environment Variables\n- `base_url`  — API base path (e.g. `http://localhost:8000/api`)\n- `token`     — JWT auth token (auto-populated after login/register)\n- `order_id`  — created order ID (auto-populated by Create Order)\n- `payment_id`— created payment ID\n\n## Auth\nAll protected requests use the Bearer token type, reading the `token` variable.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000/api"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "description": "JWT-based authentication: registration, login, profile, logout and token refresh.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{user_name}}\",\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{user_password}}\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"{{user_password}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["register"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new user account and receive a JWT token. The token is auto-saved to the `token` environment variable via the Tests script."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json && json.data && json.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('token', json.data.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token saved to the token variable.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
